+# Step-011 Names The Bad Transfer Pattern As A Tao-Style Shell-Bridging Packet Pattern
+
+Status: `INFERRED` named-target verdict with `VERIFIED` theorem-facing boundary
+
+The strongest honest bad-transfer target currently supported for the coupled
+energy-helicity branch is not a direct one-sided inequality on stretching
+production.
+
+It is a Tao-style shell-bridging packet pattern:
+
+- weak pump;
+- tiny trigger;
+- strong amplifier or rotor response;
+- delayed next-stage shell pump;
+- spectator channels lower order on the declared window.
+
+This is the right named target because the local exact-NS record is strongest
+on transfer-pattern non-isolability: geometry-fixed coefficient rigidity,
+mandatory conjugate completion, and unavoidable spectator couplings.
+
+So Step 011 can name the theorem-facing burden honestly only at the
+packet-transfer-pattern level. It still does not justify the stronger claim
+that the exact coupled ledger directly yields a coercive one-sided control on
+`omega . grad u . omega`.
+
+Filed from:
+- `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-011-exploration-002-invariant-ledger-and-tao-calibration.md`
